Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.20,0:19:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I've forgotten this all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.09,0:19:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Bob Henderson must have spent half an evening packaging it all up
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.54,0:19:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and carefully mailing it to me after a slogan press cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.79,0:19:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, so what we did in the first part of the book is the duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.20,0:19:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So we started at the bottom and we moved up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.20,0:19:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought at each lecture, I'll present, you know, one slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.11,0:19:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have a slide of the dualities that characterize each level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.27,0:19:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So today we'll start at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.48,0:19:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And then each lecture, we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.27,0:19:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.69,0:20:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So each one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.69,0:20:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now these levels aren't where we live.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.75,0:20:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody in this audience don't live there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.75,0:20:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But they are momentary.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.84,0:20:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They are transitory.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.84,0:20:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Your consciousness level can be, you know, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.84,0:20:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And suddenly you go into guilt, shame, grief, fear, desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.84,0:20:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are evanescent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.84,0:20:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So one's consciousness level is that which is dominant.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.14,0:20:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dominant.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.01,0:20:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't exclude these things coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.14,0:20:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do they come up?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.14,0:20:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They come up from the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.32,0:20:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They come up from the individual unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.20,0:20:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them are things that were projected into the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.20,0:20:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And now that you're taking spiritual responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.20,0:20:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you suddenly feel guilt about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.39,0:20:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, but that's transitory.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.39,0:20:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.31,0:20:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we should know about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.31,0:21:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we're going to cover all the levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.40,0:21:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So how many people here are new today?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.51,0:21:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.47,0:21:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the contextualization of the lecture is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.47,0:21:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to cover the basics and add something new.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.58,0:21:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We cover the basics for those who are new.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.20,0:21:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't spend a long time on it, but we do cover them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.31,0:21:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we add something new
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.34,0:21:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for the people who have been here many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.34,0:21:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So we always have a review of the old
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.23,0:21:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and an introduction of the new.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.92,0:21:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,When there isn't any more new, the lecture is stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.92,0:21:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That could be new.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.07,0:21:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing more to say other than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.24,0:21:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, folks, you're on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.49,0:22:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so what we're really doing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.38,0:22:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is presenting spiritual truth in a different context
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.38,0:22:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,than classically presented via religion
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.38,0:22:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and various spiritual...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.25,0:22:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual groups and organizations
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.38,0:22:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,which become formalized into a sort of ecclesiastic dogma,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.30,0:22:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,complete with misunderstandings of the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.30,0:22:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that was originally spoken,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.30,0:22:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but some centuries later it's misinterpreted.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.59,0:22:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And those errors stand out glaringly, glaringly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.59,0:22:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so all phenomena are happening
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.10,0:22:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of their own spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.10,0:22:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking that they're being caused by something
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.79,0:22:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is an error of perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.79,0:22:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind tries to explain phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.44,0:23:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, frankly, the mind is too dumb to explain phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.07,0:23:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't even know why a rabbit is a rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.49,0:23:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It can explain genetics, it can give you a sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.49,0:23:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are all things about, but they have nothing to do
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.49,0:23:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,with what it is to be a rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.49,0:23:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask any rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.07,0:23:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, rabbit, what is it like to be a rabbit?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.07,0:23:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, I don't know, what does rabbit mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.07,0:23:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, you don't know what a rabbit is?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.33,0:23:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Rabbit is...no.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.61,0:23:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I get the encyclopedia.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.61,0:23:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, you get me the encyclopedia.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.31,0:23:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Rabbit. Sit down, rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.31,0:23:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. I read the rabbit the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.31,0:23:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes me about 15 minutes to read all through rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.68,0:23:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I says, no. What do you think of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.11,0:23:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.11,0:23:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, that's not what I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.36,0:23:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, well, what are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.75,0:23:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, I'm me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.75,0:24:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,LAUGHTER
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.47,0:24:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're the same as the rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.47,0:24:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.35,0:24:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The rabbit, all he knows is that he's who he is, what he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.42,0:24:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all we really know.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.00,0:24:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All the rest is elaborate.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.14,0:24:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need any of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.74,0:24:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're out at sea, you have a little boat and the wind is coming up,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.15,0:24:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,what the encyclopedia says about humanity is pretty relevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.94,0:24:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You're very intensely just being who you are
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.81,0:24:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and asking God's intervention in the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.86,0:24:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So intention, then, is very powerful because the will is powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.89,0:24:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the will that sets karmic destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.32,0:24:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.65,0:25:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So to surrender to God, to commit to the Lord, to God, to divinity, to enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.50,0:25:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever you want to call it, now completely changes your future altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.66,0:25:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Completely changes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.61,0:25:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Not by virtue of causality, but by virtue of intention which changes the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.07,0:25:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything comes about as a consequence of the field and not of the linear ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.10,0:25:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,As the consequence, then, by commitment,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.08,0:25:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you've now become something different than what you were before you made the commitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.58,0:25:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a change in the barometric pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.67,0:25:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now all of the weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.15,0:25:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.18,0:25:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Not caused by anything, but as a consequence of the barometric pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.16,0:25:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the barometric pressure itself doesn't really cause anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.22,0:25:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the local condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.85,0:26:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you see, then, is potentiality becoming actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.88,0:26:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,under the circumstances that prevail at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.46,0:26:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The sea doesn't emerge until the sunlight, the warmth, and the water are appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.70,0:26:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But they don't cause the sea to.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.91,0:26:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't grow into a flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.27,0:26:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The other thing you'll notice, if you skip editing the world mentally,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.47,0:26:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is that things do not go from uncomplete to complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.84,0:26:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They do not go from imperfect to perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.84,0:26:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They go from perfect to perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.88,0:26:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All things, at all moments, are perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.19,0:26:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Imperfection is a rejection of mentalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.99,0:26:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, everything, by virtue of being what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.90,0:26:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is already perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.81,0:27:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all of creation is perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.81,0:27:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation is the unmanifest becoming manifest
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.67,0:27:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,within the experiential domain as creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.82,0:27:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation unfolds spontaneously as the consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.82,0:27:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that the source is innate to that which has been created.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.80,0:27:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of thinking of change and causality, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.80,0:27:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're witnessing is really emergence.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.80,0:27:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Emergence of potentiality becoming an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.80,0:27:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,At each moment of emergence, it's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.48,0:27:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is perfectly the fist.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.68,0:27:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is perfectly the part of the open hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.68,0:27:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This is perfectly, perfectly, perfectly, perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.79,0:27:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as the flower unfolds, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.79,0:27:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,first it's a perfect bud.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.79,0:27:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it's a perfect half-open rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.79,0:28:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it's a perfect foliar.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.79,0:28:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it's a perfectly faded rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.79,0:28:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it becomes perfect fertilizer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.83,0:28:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's perfect at every moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.83,0:28:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, things don't move from incomplete to complete
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.17,0:28:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,or from imperfection to perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.17,0:28:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They move from complete to complete
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.17,0:28:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and from perfect to perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.17,0:28:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The half-open rose is completely a half-open rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.23,0:28:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.23,0:28:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.88,0:28:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You witness that spontaneously,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.17,0:28:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,perfection prevails.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.35,0:28:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All things are manifesting
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.35,0:28:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,their potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.35,0:28:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They're only being what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.35,0:28:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And they can't be anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.09,0:29:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,To be perfectly stupid
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.09,0:29:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be perfectly stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.09,0:29:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where you're supposed to be right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.66,0:29:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Noodle-himers, we call them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.48,0:29:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.00,0:29:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we were all once children.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.00,0:29:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And because the evolution of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.57,0:29:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we have, by grace, divine grace,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.57,0:29:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,by karmic merit,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.57,0:29:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,earned the right to be
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.96,0:29:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,born a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.05,0:29:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only to have been born a human,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.05,0:29:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but to have heard of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.05,0:29:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarer still is it to have heard of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.15,0:29:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarer it is to be born a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.40,0:29:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A great karmic gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.32,0:29:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarer yet is it to have heard of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.23,0:30:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarest of all is it to have heard of enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.23,0:30:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and made the decision to seek it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.26,0:30:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, by the words of the Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.28,0:30:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,this is indeed a gifted audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.59,0:30:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And I do bow to this audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.18,0:30:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All gifted here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.00,0:30:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All here are gifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.72,0:30:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Gifted as a consequence of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.75,0:30:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Somewhere in history,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.94,0:30:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,this lifetime or sometime,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.06,0:30:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,there was made that commitment
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.06,0:30:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,by a prayer, by a declaration,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.06,0:30:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,by a devotion, by an inner decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.70,0:30:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That intention carries through forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.70,0:30:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.70,0:30:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.28,0:30:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me think it over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.28,0:31:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I meant I was going to be good for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.13,0:31:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't mean to be good all weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.13,0:31:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.48,0:31:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Saturday night included?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.04,0:31:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give the id a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.85,0:31:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Saturday night off.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.00,0:31:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Id night.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.00,0:31:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Indulgence.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.00,0:31:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Be an animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.48,0:31:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunday morning you go to church.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.48,0:31:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the whole idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.48,0:31:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What I did last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.88,0:31:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.31,0:31:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.34,0:31:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.34,0:31:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's all you really need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.34,0:31:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We could leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.34,0:31:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a letting things go
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.43,0:32:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and seeing that everything is manifesting
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.43,0:32:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,as the consequence of a field.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.43,0:32:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So the universe is an infinite,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.16,0:32:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite fields of diminishing power
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.16,0:32:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and as a consequence of that which things have become,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.64,0:32:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,like an iron filing in a magnetic field,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.64,0:32:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,each thing aligns itself where it needs to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.71,0:32:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It then emerges.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.71,0:32:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Its potentiality then emerges as an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.71,0:32:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,if conditions are appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.16,0:32:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no necessity to even conjure up
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.16,0:32:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,an intellectual axiom such as causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.27,0:32:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Causality is an explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.27,0:32:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Calvary is at 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.44,0:32:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual truth, you know, really starts around 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.44,0:32:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.44,0:32:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore you have why science
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.44,0:32:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and spirituality,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.44,0:32:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,what's the relationship with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.44,0:32:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,during me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.44,0:33:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.44,0:33:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.44,0:33:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're going to recapitulate.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.44,0:33:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll start with slide one.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.44,0:33:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we're going to move through rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.78,0:33:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Move through rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.40,0:33:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Move through rapidly, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.40,0:33:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to move through rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.33,0:33:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we now have a total of 60 slides to select from.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.33,0:33:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And we thought eventually we'll put out a book
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.59,0:33:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of slides and charts, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.59,0:33:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Slides and charts.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.59,0:33:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people have asked for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.59,0:33:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Just slides and charts.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.59,0:33:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to read all that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.81,0:33:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you just get it in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.81,0:33:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.81,0:33:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.94,0:33:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So this, of course, is very well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.94,0:33:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We've explained it many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.94,0:33:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,These have to do with the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.94,0:33:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a logarithmic number.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.94,0:33:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, as consciousness advances,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.94,0:33:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,it advances more and more rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.94,0:33:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the beginning, it's slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.94,0:33:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you move along,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.94,0:33:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be surprised by a very sudden
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.94,0:34:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,jumps in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.94,0:34:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.94,0:34:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell people what they need to know
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.94,0:34:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,way along the pathway early.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.97,0:34:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't talk about the void today,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.96,0:34:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's another thing we have to tell you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.96,0:34:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And the temptations that come along the way
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.96,0:34:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,where people fall off the pedestal, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.28,0:34:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because each spiritual student, in a way,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.28,0:34:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is tested too, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.28,0:34:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like there's something evil out there testing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.28,0:34:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that quality of the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.28,0:34:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that quality of the ego which seeks to persist.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.76,0:34:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.92,0:34:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to be kind and benevolent to everybody,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.92,0:34:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,instantly a dog bites your ankle.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.92,0:34:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego says,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.05,0:34:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I win.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.98,0:34:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Not going to get away from my clutches.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.28,0:34:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Whose clutches are you in?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.28,0:35:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I say the clutches of the primitive narcissistic ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.59,0:35:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The world would like to label it evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.59,0:35:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,bad, the devil, Satan.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.59,0:35:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it all kinds of personifications
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.59,0:35:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and then live in fear of their own personifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.51,0:35:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in science there's what is called
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.63,0:35:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,sufficient explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.63,0:35:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So we will supply sufficient explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.76,0:35:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need anything magical
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.76,0:35:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to superimpose on it or mythical.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.76,0:35:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the evolution of consciousness here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.98,0:35:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And it demonstrates itself throughout humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.98,0:35:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Each level is accompanied by a prevailing emotional state.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.36,0:35:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Heavenly, blissful, happy, less and less happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.51,0:35:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The process of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.67,0:35:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the process of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.67,0:36:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,At the top we have illumination.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.67,0:36:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Down here we have inflation.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.67,0:36:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.67,0:36:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You ever watch TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.94,0:36:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what happens in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.94,0:36:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody has to get on and give you their opinion of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.94,0:36:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I want to know his opinion for?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.09,0:36:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the American way.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.09,0:36:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.32,0:36:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And enslavement by addictions, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.32,0:36:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.32,0:36:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.38,0:36:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So we call these different levels,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.38,0:36:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we describe them in emotional terms
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.38,0:36:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because that is the most commonly understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.38,0:36:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The view of the self is quite different.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.38,0:36:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,These people hate themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.38,0:36:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they project their hatred onto the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.38,0:36:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,see evil out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.28,0:36:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you move up here,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.28,0:36:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the view of self becomes more and more positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.28,0:36:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,More and more positive,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.28,0:36:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally you're comfortable with yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.28,0:36:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The view of God then is a correlation
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.28,0:36:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,with your level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.28,0:36:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,At the bottom you have the demonic depictions of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.28,0:37:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the anthropomorphic projections
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.28,0:37:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in which God is punitive,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.28,0:37:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,he's partial,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.28,0:37:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,he's got favoritism,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.28,0:37:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and you've got to be afraid of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.44,0:37:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the God of terror,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.44,0:37:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which is really satanic.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.44,0:37:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a satanic depiction of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.78,0:37:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,These are satanic.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.51,0:37:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the qualities of Satan,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.51,0:37:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,not divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.55,0:37:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, their introduction
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.59,0:37:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in the New Testament,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.59,0:37:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Book of Revelations,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.88,0:37:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and in many chapters of the Old Testament,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.90,0:37:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,are of the anthropomorphic God of primitivism.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.15,0:37:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Storms, you assuage the storms,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.15,0:37:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the gods were angry,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.15,0:37:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the gods were angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.44,0:37:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Even today, end times predictions
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.44,0:37:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,are always coming around.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.80,0:37:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And religious tracts that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.80,0:37:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,describe everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.80,0:37:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsunamis and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.80,0:37:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There's predictions from the Bible, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.05,0:37:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I always point out
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.05,0:37:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that greater disasters
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.05,0:37:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that have occurred in the history of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.05,0:37:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,occurred before mankind was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.38,0:38:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Earthquakes were here before man was here, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.51,0:38:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thugs were here before.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.51,0:38:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All those phenomena, in fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.51,0:38:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,they're supposedly what wiped out the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.51,0:38:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a natural disaster
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.88,0:38:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that ostensibly knocked out the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.88,0:38:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So unless God was angry at the dinosaurs,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.88,0:38:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how to explain it in Biblical terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.88,0:38:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, that kind of a God,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.76,0:38:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you eventually leave that kind of negative viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.76,0:38:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of the Gothic downside of religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.76,0:38:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why a lot of people become spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.76,0:38:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They know that somewhere within religion
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.76,0:38:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,there's spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.76,0:38:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But they find a lot of the teachings
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.76,0:38:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,confining and intuitively not in alignment
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.82,0:38:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,with that which is infinite truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.94,0:38:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is infinitely merciful.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.94,0:38:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is infinitely merciful is what?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.19,0:38:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's infinitely merciful.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.19,0:38:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.19,0:38:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So your view of God, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.21,0:39:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,has nothing to do with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.21,0:39:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with your level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.21,0:39:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You see him as merciful, wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.21,0:39:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You see him as a source of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.21,0:39:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of oneness, of all-beingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.21,0:39:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, divinity itself shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.15,0:39:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,To transcend these levels of consciousness is,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.26,0:39:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the book I just read,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.26,0:39:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I just got through finishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.26,0:39:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I said there's an upside and downside
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.26,0:39:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that holds each of these levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.26,0:39:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This level is always looking for gain, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.38,0:39:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's based on feeling incomplete.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.38,0:39:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When you understand the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.38,0:39:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you see everything is going from complete to complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.57,0:39:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is complete and perfect right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.86,0:39:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here is just completely,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.86,0:39:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,completely the perfect manifestation
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.86,0:39:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of your total karmic evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.86,0:39:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,up to this point in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.88,0:40:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to be dissatisfied with about yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.88,0:40:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,except impatience.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.40,0:40:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I wish I was there instead of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.88,0:40:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.88,0:40:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no problem other than impatience, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.13,0:40:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone here is destined to become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.13,0:40:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We've checked this group out before.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.69,0:40:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't sell them a ticket, otherwise...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.88,0:40:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone in this room is destined for enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.88,0:40:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.44,0:41:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We've checked that over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.48,0:41:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.48,0:41:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Who else but a future golfer would be at a golf class?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.96,0:41:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't attend golf classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.96,0:41:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not destined to be a golf star.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.19,0:41:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No, people here are here because of their intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.30,0:41:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the lecture today, intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.36,0:41:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.51,0:41:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody wrote a book called The Power of Intention recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.51,0:41:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.51,0:41:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, I read the last chapter
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.51,0:41:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was free off the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.55,0:41:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but The Power of Intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.55,0:41:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right, now let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.65,0:41:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go to the next slide, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.38,0:41:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.21,0:41:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.44,0:41:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason why intention is so powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.44,0:42:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll get to the mechanics of it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.44,0:42:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for people who are still stuck
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.44,0:42:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,with being intelligent and rational and educated.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.88,0:42:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason intention is so powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.73,0:42:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do, of course, within this domain
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.96,0:42:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.96,0:42:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So we will connect up science, quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.96,0:42:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.96,0:42:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and connect up the Buddha and Einstein
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.96,0:42:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and Heisenberg all at once, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.38,0:42:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the higher states of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.38,0:42:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, the last chart goes up to 600
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.67,0:42:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,because that covers about 99% of the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.67,0:42:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,99.9%, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.21,0:42:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, but from 600 up then,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.25,0:42:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,what are the more advanced levels
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.25,0:43:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and what do we call them?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.25,0:43:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Enlightenment is typically 600 and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.25,0:43:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Classically, once you hit the state of bliss,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.25,0:43:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,satchitananda, bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.51,0:43:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,At bliss, about half the people leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.21,0:43:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's today on.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.78,0:43:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless somebody comes and gets you,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.19,0:43:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you probably just dehydrate and fall over,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.19,0:43:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.67,0:43:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But the world gets excited about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.67,0:43:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,so the world comes along and the cops tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.67,0:43:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't sit on the rock anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.67,0:43:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,People tell you you haven't eaten since Tuesday,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.67,0:43:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,so they force food on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.67,0:43:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so 600 is the level of satchitananda,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.67,0:43:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.67,0:43:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.67,0:44:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's complete and total within itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.00,0:44:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no need for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.00,0:44:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no desire for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.00,0:44:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether the physicality continues or not
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.00,0:44:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is totally irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.48,0:44:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's no inclination to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.76,0:44:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you survive that, you get up into the 700s,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.76,0:44:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which is Ramana Maharshi, Nisargadatta Maharaj,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.92,0:44:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and one who did manage to survive
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.92,0:44:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and reenter the world was Mother Teresa,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.23,0:44:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,who also demonstrates 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.78,0:44:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,These states get higher and higher,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.78,0:44:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally we reach states that are extremely unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.78,0:44:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Extremely unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.78,0:44:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When they occur, they usually have an historic impact
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.78,0:44:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,on the destiny of mankind for centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.80,0:45:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So the impact of the Avatar has been
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.03,0:45:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to totally design all of society down
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.03,0:45:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,through the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.05,0:45:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's spiritual truth that gives ethics,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.59,0:45:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,law, reason, all its integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.98,0:45:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So in Europe what's happened now is
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.98,0:45:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual truth which came out of
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.59,0:45:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that particular religion and structured the society,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.59,0:45:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,now it refutes the source of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.65,0:45:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and it becomes, it calls itself secular.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.94,0:45:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.32,0:45:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we know how to do that on our own,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.32,0:45:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't need you folks anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.32,0:45:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So they sort of said goodbye to the church.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.00,0:45:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But so out of those spiritual truths then,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.00,0:45:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,all of society, the energy is so powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.71,0:45:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,at a thousand or 850, 950 thousand,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.71,0:46:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it's so powerful that it contextualizes
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.71,0:46:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,all of society permanently, permanently you want to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.15,0:46:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can refute its source,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.63,0:46:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but you still are what it created.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.63,0:46:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The Congress, whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.15,0:46:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the law that you call forth
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.21,0:46:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to back up your rights,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.23,0:46:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,came out of religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.23,0:46:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can refute the religion,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.23,0:46:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but the truth of the structure that came out of it survives.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.30,0:46:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the power of the Avatar.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.80,0:46:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,On this planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.80,0:46:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it's very difficult to live beyond 600,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.80,0:46:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond 700, beyond 800.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.90,0:46:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.90,0:46:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,850 is very difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.96,0:46:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And it only happens very occasionally.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.96,0:46:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,When it does,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.96,0:46:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it's by some divine intervention.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.44,0:47:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And the stress on the nervous system is extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.44,0:47:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,From 800 and up,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.67,0:47:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the stress on the nervous system is extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.67,0:47:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.71,0:47:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And then so on this planet then,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.71,0:47:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually you leave and we ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.71,0:47:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, what is an archangel?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.71,0:47:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,An archangel calibrates at 50,000 and up.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.98,0:47:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I once sent out a prayer that was answered by,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.98,0:47:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.76,0:47:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to say this here.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.76,0:47:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That prayer was an archangel.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.84,0:47:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.84,0:47:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.84,0:47:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the pits of hell,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.84,0:47:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which I've described elsewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.84,0:47:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,which are forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.94,0:47:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the pits of hell are beyond anyone's imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.94,0:47:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And they are infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.94,0:47:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.94,0:47:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.94,0:47:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's foreverness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.94,0:47:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of that arose a voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.94,0:47:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It said,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.94,0:47:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is a God,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.19,0:47:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask him for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.19,0:48:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And then everything that one had been was eliminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.44,0:48:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And then shone forth the glory of divinity as all of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.90,0:48:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The thought was picked up by,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.90,0:48:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I always call it a cruising archangel.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.90,0:48:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A cruising archangel just picked up the thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.28,0:48:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,gave it a second's notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.28,0:48:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This life was totally,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.28,0:48:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,totally changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.28,0:48:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't want to mess with archangels.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.15,0:48:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's have the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.88,0:48:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's like divinity is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.88,0:48:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then like progressive levels,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.96,0:48:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the power,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.96,0:48:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you call those things,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.07,0:48:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the British power,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.07,0:48:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.15,0:48:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.15,0:48:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,like diminishing transformers.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.15,0:49:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So the archangels are extremely high.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.15,0:49:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we consider the highest on this planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.15,0:49:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I always suspect is like kindergarten
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.15,0:49:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and other dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.38,0:49:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.38,0:49:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,don't mess with archangels.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.21,0:49:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the world's population is distribution,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.21,0:49:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,which we'll understand when we see how the ego evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.23,0:49:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.34,0:49:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,approximately 80% of the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.34,0:49:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is below the level of integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.34,0:49:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,80% of the people who walk this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.34,0:49:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,are run by the animal ego
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.34,0:49:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to get the best of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.71,0:49:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to see you as competition,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.32,0:49:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to hate you without feeling guilty about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.32,0:49:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lifestyle,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.78,0:49:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,then,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.78,0:49:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in 80% of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.23,0:49:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the distribution of levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.23,0:49:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.46,0:49:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,very few people are maintaining a balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.46,0:50:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And without them,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.46,0:50:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,civilization would probably destruct.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.46,0:50:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Civilization would destruct.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.46,0:50:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's see if that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.46,0:50:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask this here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.07,0:50:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the top 15%,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.07,0:50:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,civilization would self-destruct.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.07,0:50:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Civilization would self-destruct
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.19,0:50:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,if it wasn't for those people of integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.19,0:50:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How does that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.19,0:50:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens because their consciousness is so powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.19,0:50:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This never got colored in.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.26,0:50:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Their consciousness is so powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.59,0:50:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that they balance the other 80% of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.59,0:50:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,without which the 80% of the world would self-destruct.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.59,0:50:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw it come close, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.94,0:50:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember when Russia had the mega-bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.94,0:50:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that would destroy all of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.94,0:50:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and in case Russia lost an atomic war,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.11,0:50:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,ballistic war,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.15,0:50:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the final solution bomb would destroy all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.15,0:51:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler tried it with Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.61,0:51:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Megalomania,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.98,0:51:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,narcissistic megalomania,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.98,0:51:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the great rulers,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.98,0:51:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,come close over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.98,0:51:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, in my lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.34,0:51:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,100 million people have died in war,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.34,0:51:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,all as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.71,0:51:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So what keeps then this
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.82,0:51:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,from totally destroying life
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.82,0:51:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is that there is
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.82,0:51:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of people
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.82,0:51:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping them afloat.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.82,0:51:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one of the jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.48,0:51:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the jobs that you have
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.48,0:51:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is by being what you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.48,0:51:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you counterbalance enormous negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.48,0:51:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We once calculated
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.48,0:51:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,one person at 400
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.48,0:51:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,compensates for, I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.48,0:51:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,1,000 people below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.48,0:51:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,At 500, you compensate for maybe 10,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.51,0:51:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,By 600, you're holding up millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.51,0:51:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the evolution of consciousness over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.13,0:52:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, at the time of the Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.13,0:52:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it was at 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.13,0:52:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of Jesus Christ,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.13,0:52:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness level of mankind was 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.13,0:52:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It came up slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.03,0:52:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 190 for centuries, centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.09,0:52:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All of European history was at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.09,0:52:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And now it went up to 205.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.09,0:52:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's up to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.09,0:52:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So people will say, well, what is the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.11,0:52:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if this is the way consciousness is going,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.11,0:52:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks like the future is optimistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.11,0:52:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So forget about the end times, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.11,0:52:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The future looks very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.69,0:52:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.30,0:52:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I like this slide
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.88,0:52:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,because the difficulty,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.13,0:52:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason people leave religion
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.13,0:52:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is often out of guilt and sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.13,0:52:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,When I became an atheist,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.13,0:52:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a huge relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.13,0:53:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was, I told you, I was very religious.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.36,0:53:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was an acolyte, a boy soloist.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.07,0:53:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I was religious to the point of scrupulosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.07,0:53:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They sent me to the, to the priests
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.17,0:53:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to be counseled about scrupulosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.78,0:53:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I lived in dread and fear of sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.78,0:53:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.78,0:53:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Because sin was explained to me as a blot on your soul
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.78,0:53:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and God can see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.78,0:53:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God, if that doesn't throw you into paranoia,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.78,0:53:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you think the thought darn.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.78,0:53:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We weren't even supposed to say darn when I was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.90,0:53:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Darn.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.90,0:53:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.90,0:53:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There goes the splat.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.90,0:53:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,God sees you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.44,0:53:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell you, life was tough, especially in adolescence.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.44,0:53:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Guys will know what that means.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.38,0:53:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All of it was no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.71,0:53:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole subject was no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.71,0:54:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole subject and all expressions thereof was sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.76,0:54:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's tough to live with at 18, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.44,0:54:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the interpretation then of the animal instincts
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.94,0:54:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,became, I call it the Gothic viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.94,0:54:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,became sackcloth sin and penance
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.98,0:54:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and fasting all during Lent and all kinds of miserable things.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.98,0:54:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then one day walking through the woods,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.50,0:54:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I've related before,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.50,0:54:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,not thinking of anything at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.69,0:54:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful day in the woods,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.88,0:54:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the stillness and silence emerged
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.88,0:54:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,like a presentation,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.26,0:54:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,a knowingness of the totality
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.26,0:54:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of the suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.26,0:55:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of all of mankind throughout all of the ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.26,0:55:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The totality of the suffering of all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.44,0:55:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A profound shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.44,0:55:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Profound shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.48,0:55:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.48,0:55:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Right to the center of my being almost.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.48,0:55:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In that instant I became an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.23,0:55:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I cannot because in those days people thought
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.23,0:55:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,God created everything, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.01,0:55:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a personal act,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.17,0:55:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but decided so.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.55,0:55:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So I held God responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.59,0:55:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course the spiritual error was
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.59,0:55:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I was seeing the consequences of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.98,0:55:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and I held God responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.98,0:55:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for what the ego had created for man.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.98,0:55:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The current catastrophes in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.71,0:56:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,are the consequence of the human ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.71,0:56:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time I would have blamed it on God.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.09,0:56:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I became a rabid atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.09,0:56:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a ferocious atheist too.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.55,0:56:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I got straight A in theology,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.55,0:56:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,straight A in the ethics,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.55,0:56:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,straight A in Thomas Aquinas.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.55,0:56:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All the time I was an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.15,0:56:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The arguments for the existence of God
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.69,0:56:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,as first cause is idiotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.69,0:56:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It is idiotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.90,0:56:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw that this morning in our opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.90,0:56:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no first cause which would
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.90,0:56:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,make God linear with a beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.90,0:56:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and an ending and an elsewhere-ness.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.90,0:56:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever-ness is forever-ness.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.98,0:56:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have any start.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.98,0:56:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So then I was free of the downside,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.55,0:56:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the interpretation of the animal instincts.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.55,0:56:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Their depiction is evil
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.55,0:56:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you have to feel guilt and shame
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.55,0:56:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and penance and all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.55,0:57:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And also you get addicted to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.55,0:57:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Curiously, when you depict it that way
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.55,0:57:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it is now more difficult to get rid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.55,0:57:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you have given it importance
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.55,0:57:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and strength and prominence
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.55,0:57:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which it doesn't have in and of itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.73,0:57:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How did this arise then?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.73,0:57:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What the world calls sin and evil
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.88,0:57:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is really the prevalence of the animal ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.88,0:57:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.88,0:57:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Selfishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.88,0:57:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we look how life evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.88,0:57:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in the very beginning,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.88,0:57:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that life,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.05,0:57:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to survive on this planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.05,0:57:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,had to have the capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.46,0:57:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to acquire energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.01,0:57:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the characteristic
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.61,0:57:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of your ego right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.61,0:57:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The leading edge of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.61,0:57:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is what I call the experiencer,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.61,0:57:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,which we'll get to later.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.78,0:57:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It is constantly searching,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.78,0:57:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,searching, searching, searching.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.78,0:58:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at Technicolor movies
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.71,0:58:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,from the bottom of the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.71,0:58:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,incredibly beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.86,0:58:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The incredible beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.86,0:58:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that exists down there,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.86,0:58:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,every single thing there is incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.86,0:58:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see that everything there
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.73,0:58:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,has exactly one function.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.73,0:58:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obsessed with getting, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.71,0:58:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Even my cat's always at the dish.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.92,0:58:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, what the hell is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.92,0:58:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you some kind of an eating machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.53,0:58:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fur-covered eating machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.88,0:58:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He's eaten four times today
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.59,0:58:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and now he's at his bowl.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.59,0:58:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Meow, meow.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.59,0:58:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so now here we have
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.13,0:58:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibrated level of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.13,0:59:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it at its emergence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.13,0:59:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we picked you up
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.42,0:59:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and threw you onto Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.42,0:59:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,your survival is what you're about, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.42,0:59:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Your survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.59,0:59:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going to get oxygen?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.59,0:59:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going to get water?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.59,0:59:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going to get
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.59,0:59:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what you need to survive?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.59,0:59:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ego has to do with get.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.59,0:59:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Get, get.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.59,0:59:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees itself as insufficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.59,0:59:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.59,0:59:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Bacteria start at one.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.59,0:59:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Algae don't calibrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.19,0:59:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrate at one.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.44,0:59:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Marine invertebrates at eight,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.44,0:59:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,like a trilobite.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.44,0:59:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You get the early fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.01,0:59:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Scorpions.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.01,0:59:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Scorpions have been around
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.01,0:59:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,for 40, 400 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.01,0:59:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They climbed out of the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.28,0:59:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and hang out causing trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.88,0:59:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people like scorpions.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.03,0:59:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless them.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.19,0:59:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You sit on one,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.19,1:00:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll see how you change your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.53,1:00:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They're at 17.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.53,1:00:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you get amphibians,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.53,1:00:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the great sharks,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.53,1:00:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the great white sharks,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.53,1:00:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the first reptiles,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.53,1:00:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the mirage of reptiles.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.53,1:00:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.67,1:00:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Bony fishes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.67,1:00:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The first birds.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.67,1:00:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have birds.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.73,1:00:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And primitive mammals.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.23,1:00:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.23,1:00:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it took,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.23,1:00:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,these are archeologic ages,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.23,1:00:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.30,1:00:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Like 1,300 billion years
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.30,1:00:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,or something,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.30,1:00:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which I can't even comprehend anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.30,1:00:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll go to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.30,1:00:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how life evolved then.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.34,1:00:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,These are not sinful.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.40,1:00:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not sinful.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.65,1:00:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The scorpion fish,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.65,1:00:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.65,1:00:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,he just eats things.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.84,1:00:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.84,1:00:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have bacteria,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.84,1:00:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,protozoa,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.84,1:00:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,insects,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.84,1:00:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,fish,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.84,1:00:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,sharks.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.84,1:01:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have the Komodo dragon at 40.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.84,1:01:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Reptiles.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.30,1:01:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You see these are all,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.30,1:01:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we picture them as predatory.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.30,1:01:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all predatory.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.36,1:01:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The birds of prey,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.36,1:01:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the rhinoceros.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.36,1:01:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you get higher and higher and higher.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.36,1:01:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And now at 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.36,1:01:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you suddenly see a shift of lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.36,1:01:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You run into the giraffe,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.36,1:01:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the zebra,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.36,1:01:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the gazelle,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.36,1:01:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the deer.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.40,1:01:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And they do not live by predation.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.40,1:01:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't kill anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.07,1:01:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So these animals here are higher than,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.07,1:01:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you're safer here
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.07,1:01:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,than you are with 80% of the people on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.07,1:01:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A giraffe will leave you alone
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.34,1:01:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you just go around with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.34,1:01:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he'll give you a kick.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.34,1:01:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But he doesn't eat you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.88,1:01:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The giraffe doesn't come over
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.51,1:01:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and hit you over the head
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.51,1:01:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and knock you unconscious
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.51,1:01:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and begin to nibble on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.51,1:01:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He just says,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.40,1:01:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you're in my territory.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.40,1:02:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoop.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.40,1:02:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There he goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.71,1:02:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know who thought up a giraffe.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.19,1:02:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They had a sense of humor,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.19,1:02:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.19,1:02:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Some archangel,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.19,1:02:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,some blade.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.92,1:02:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They have a design studio
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.92,1:02:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere up in heaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.92,1:02:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I already think of this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.38,1:02:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, elephants,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.38,1:02:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you gotta be a little cautious with elephants.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.38,1:02:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They won't eat you either.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.38,1:02:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But they may sit on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.61,1:02:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we have kitty cats,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.40,1:02:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,family cats.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.40,1:02:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how it evolves.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.40,1:02:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the chimpanzee
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.40,1:02:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,who has 99 point something,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.40,1:02:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the same DNA as we do.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.40,1:02:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you see
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.73,1:02:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness evolves
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.73,1:02:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,from severely predacious,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.73,1:02:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,savage,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.73,1:02:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,inconsiderate of the life of others,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.73,1:03:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,then these people begin to form families.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.73,1:03:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the emergence of maternal care.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.73,1:03:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we get up to the highest levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.76,1:03:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.17,1:03:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we always like to mention
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.17,1:03:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,a dog's wagging tail is 500
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.17,1:03:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and a cat's fur is 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.17,1:03:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,A songbird's song is 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.17,1:03:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And a great parrot, Alex,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.34,1:03:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is exceptionally smarter than broccoli.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.78,1:03:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he should.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.11,1:03:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a PhD.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.11,1:03:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We spent years training him.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.11,1:03:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli had somebody like that,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.03,1:03:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,year in and year out.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.51,1:03:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see where broccoli is.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.53,1:03:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli's over 350.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.53,1:03:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,355.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.53,1:03:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli's sort of stuck there,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.01,1:03:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,around 350.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.30,1:03:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, the purpose of seeing all this.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.30,1:03:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next slide?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.30,1:03:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.30,1:03:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next slide, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.36,1:04:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.09,1:04:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm trying to display then
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.09,1:04:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.42,1:04:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, well, we'll save that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.42,1:04:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll flip that off for a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.42,1:04:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so what we want to get out of all of this
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.63,1:04:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the essence of life is to get.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.76,1:04:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no point in feeling guilty about your ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.15,1:04:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,selfishness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.15,1:04:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to be selfish
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.15,1:04:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,up to a point,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.53,1:04:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,up to consciousness level 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.53,1:04:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's supposed to run you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.53,1:04:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200, it's still,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.96,1:04:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is a tendency.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.96,1:04:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.96,1:04:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.96,1:04:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not where you live.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.96,1:04:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not your,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.96,1:04:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the way you live.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.96,1:04:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't live in a predatory manner.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.96,1:04:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There are parts of the world that calibrate 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.36,1:04:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole contextualization of their society is predacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.36,1:04:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you get off the plane,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.59,1:05:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,they're selling you stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.59,1:05:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They're fake,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.59,1:05:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,fake antiques.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.63,1:05:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, how much is it to ride on a plane?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.78,1:05:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, how much is it to ride on this camel?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.78,1:05:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Five dollars.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.48,1:05:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.15,1:05:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time to get off the camel.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.40,1:05:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever tried getting off a camel?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.92,1:05:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no idea how tall,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.92,1:05:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,way up in the air a camel is.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.92,1:05:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You think of it like a big horse.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.92,1:05:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A camel is up where that ceiling is.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.53,1:05:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you want to get off.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.84,1:05:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you going to get off a camel without a ladder?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.09,1:05:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.28,1:05:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So I say to the camel driver,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.28,1:05:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,okay,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.34,1:05:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that's enough ride for you today.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.34,1:05:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'll get down.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.44,1:05:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll be ten dollars, he says.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.15,1:05:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I contracted five dollars for the camel ride.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.34,1:05:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he wants ten to get off the camel.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.34,1:06:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize that's a matter of honor with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.53,1:06:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a matter of honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.17,1:06:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The naivete of international diplomacy just blows my mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.17,1:06:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't get into that today.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.40,1:06:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not know who you're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.55,1:06:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a matter of pride.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.82,1:06:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody in that culture
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.82,1:06:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that pays an asking price
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.82,1:06:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,lives in shame henceforth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.59,1:06:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Being nice to them
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.59,1:06:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is considered weakness, idiocy,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.07,1:06:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and you deserve to die
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.07,1:06:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.07,1:06:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's today's world.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.53,1:06:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.26,1:06:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So this animal then, instinct,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.26,1:06:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,operates in the human brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.59,1:07:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the evolutionary time,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.59,1:07:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the prefrontal cortex,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.59,1:07:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,when the hominid arose,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.59,1:07:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,he got up on two hind feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.59,1:07:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And now he had two more limbs.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.61,1:07:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.61,1:07:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He had that,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.61,1:07:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you got four limbs,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.61,1:07:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,they're all busy just,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.61,1:07:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.61,1:07:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,walking around.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.61,1:07:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What time did we quit?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.71,1:07:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.34,1:07:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,1115?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.80,1:07:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.80,1:07:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.80,1:07:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the hominid then emerges.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.80,1:07:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing emerges independent of the evolutionary tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.80,1:07:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.80,1:07:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes to its linear designation,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.80,1:07:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,occurs in the level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.80,1:07:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you can't find
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.80,1:07:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,any missing links in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.80,1:07:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because there aren't any.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.80,1:07:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There aren't any missing links in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.80,1:07:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution of consciousness is within,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.98,1:07:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution is within consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.98,1:07:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it manifests out
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.98,1:07:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and manifests
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.98,1:07:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and it manifests in physicality.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.98,1:07:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So the evolution of the ego then
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.03,1:08:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is that quality of life
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.15,1:08:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,since it began.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.15,1:08:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Since life began.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.38,1:08:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see why spiritual work is difficult.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.38,1:08:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're trying to overcome
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.38,1:08:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,patterns that have
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.61,1:08:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,consolidated over millennia,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.61,1:08:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,over millennia.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.61,1:08:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.55,1:08:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside of human nature,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.55,1:08:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,what we call the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.55,1:08:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,sin, guilt,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.55,1:08:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,all the things that we
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.55,1:08:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,struggle to overcome and transcend,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.55,1:08:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,judgmentalism,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.55,1:08:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,vindictiveness,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.55,1:08:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.55,1:08:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,are all qualities of our,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.68,1:08:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of our evolutionary,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.36,1:08:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of our evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.39,1:08:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we do then,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.39,1:08:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of vilifying it,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.39,1:08:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling guilt,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.39,1:08:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,blaming yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.39,1:08:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,see,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.39,1:08:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,if you blame yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.39,1:08:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,then you got to project that onto the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.39,1:08:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're the ones that are causing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.39,1:08:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, they're the ones.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.39,1:08:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you have to attack and kill them.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.60,1:08:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What would the world be without that?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.60,1:09:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing to do, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.65,1:09:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Kept mankind busy
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.65,1:09:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and throughout the history of civilization,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.23,1:09:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.23,1:09:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,peace has reigned 7% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.23,1:09:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,7% of man's history
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.81,1:09:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,has been at peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.81,1:09:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,93% of the time
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.84,1:09:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we're at war.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.84,1:09:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,93%.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.18,1:09:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.76,1:09:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So peace is in a natural condition.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.92,1:09:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people hate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.92,1:09:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people hate peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.88,1:09:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.88,1:09:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.11,1:09:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,if you forgive this guy,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.11,1:09:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd be at peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.11,1:09:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, he don't deserve it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.11,1:09:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He just refused peace, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.89,1:09:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,People refuse peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.89,1:09:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They really hate peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.89,1:09:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They really hate peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.89,1:09:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.89,1:09:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in the condition of peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.89,1:09:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,they're nobody.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.65,1:09:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In a non-peaceful situation,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.65,1:10:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you get to be somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.65,1:10:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to wear daggers.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.75,1:10:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to be the killer, bravado.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.60,1:10:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to be in charge.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.60,1:10:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.93,1:10:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You're somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.56,1:10:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,After the war is over,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.56,1:10:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,who are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.21,1:10:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You're an ex-admiral.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.21,1:10:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.59,1:10:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so I just want you
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.59,1:10:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to get a benign view of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.59,1:10:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,before we get into the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.59,1:10:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at it as benign.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.64,1:10:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.64,1:10:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.64,1:10:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.64,1:10:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.64,1:10:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If your cat gets into the fish
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.64,1:10:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you brought home from dinner
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.64,1:10:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and eats it,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.64,1:10:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't being evil.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.64,1:10:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have to wear
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.64,1:10:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,sackcloth and ashes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.64,1:10:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have to go to confession.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.64,1:10:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the kitty being a kitty.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.72,1:10:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want you to love your ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.76,1:10:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I brought ego with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.80,1:11:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You always want something.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.57,1:11:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way I'm brought up.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.77,1:11:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If I get mad at it, I chew it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.67,1:11:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, he bites it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.67,1:11:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.67,1:11:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Aggression, that is innate.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.18,1:11:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So all the qualities that we work to overcome.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.56,1:11:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because when the prefrontal cortex evolved,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.03,1:11:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the hominids took it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.03,1:11:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he's got two limbs to do something with.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.03,1:11:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He got an opposing thumb.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.03,1:11:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually they have an opposing thumb.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.03,1:11:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was still there, for God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.27,1:11:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, with an opposing thumb,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.60,1:11:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,now he can handle tools.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.60,1:11:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And the prefrontal cortex
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.60,1:11:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,became more and more complex.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.60,1:11:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But the prefrontal cortex
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.07,1:11:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't replace the old animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.07,1:11:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just put there on top of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.07,1:11:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can figure clever ways
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.52,1:11:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to kill your enemies.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.52,1:12:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Clever, intelligent ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.52,1:12:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Atomic bombs.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.52,1:12:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So now what you have is an animal
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.52,1:12:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that can think and is intelligent.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.52,1:12:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's really dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.52,1:12:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.65,1:12:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're going to take a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.65,1:12:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're going to resume.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.65,1:12:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Resume?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.65,1:12:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Resume.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.65,1:12:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to resume at what time?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.61,1:12:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.61,1:12:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to resume in 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.77,1:12:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And again, we're going to give the best part of the lecture
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.31,1:12:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.31,1:12:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're late, you'll miss it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.31,1:12:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to wash my mouth.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.17,1:12:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I was soaked.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.17,1:12:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Where were we?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.89,1:12:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We were at...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.11,1:12:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We were ready for the great books
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.11,1:12:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of the rest of the world, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.11,1:12:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.68,1:12:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We've gone over a number of these things
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.01,1:13:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of times.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.03,1:13:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, repetition.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.03,1:13:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Repetition.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.03,1:13:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,After you've heard a thing enough times,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.03,1:13:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to understand or think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.03,1:13:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You just know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.03,1:13:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want to save you the problem of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.03,1:13:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I've repeated it often enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.84,1:13:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be handy when you try to clear guilt, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.06,1:13:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Because guilt has to do with demonizing the animal kingdom
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.19,1:13:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,within yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.40,1:13:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.40,1:13:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness, you see how it evolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.40,1:13:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it came a long way.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.40,1:13:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, in the 400s, you see the world of the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.40,1:13:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,which is, of course, the blessings of the intellect
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.56,1:13:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,are civilization and science and pharmacology,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.72,1:13:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the electronic...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.72,1:13:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I won't mention the electronic world, but anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.72,1:13:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.10,1:14:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We calibrated every one.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.73,1:14:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You see they run in the mid-400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.73,1:14:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Occasionally, somebody gets to the high 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.73,1:14:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Notable is Einstein, Freud, Sir Isaac Newton at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.14,1:14:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's genius as far as the intellect can go.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.72,1:14:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a paradigm jump at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.72,1:14:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is difficult for people to comprehend.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.72,1:14:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.03,1:14:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The world from 500 up is of context and not content.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.03,1:14:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So the jump from the limitation of causality
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.03,1:14:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,means you have to jump the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.03,1:14:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hegel...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.09,1:14:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Hegel at 470?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.15,1:14:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a couple of favorites here.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.15,1:14:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hegel, because one of Hegel's principles,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.25,1:14:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that was in Germany,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.25,1:14:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the high point of the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.50,1:14:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the great philosophers of Germany.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.94,1:15:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hegel postulated the concept
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.94,1:15:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of the principle of the absolute,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.94,1:15:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the absolute,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.75,1:15:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,which is in diametric opposition
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.75,1:15:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to today's modernistic, postmodernism,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.71,1:15:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to substitute relativism.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.71,1:15:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativism really says there is no God.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.71,1:15:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It really says that.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.00,1:15:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of them say it overtly.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.00,1:15:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Others do it just more sneakily.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.38,1:15:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That everything is only what you say it is
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.38,1:15:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,or think it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.40,1:15:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Which also negates the Cartesian principle.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.40,1:15:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So the modern world,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.40,1:15:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the social contention,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.40,1:15:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is based on relativism,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.67,1:15:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates quite low.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.67,1:15:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.78,1:15:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the biggest proponent of relativism
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.78,1:15:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,was Karl Marx.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.78,1:15:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And Karl Marx, you see, stands out.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.81,1:16:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here is in the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.17,1:16:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,even into 505, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.17,1:16:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a great Schroesser, a Descartes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.17,1:16:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All the great minds of history are here.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.32,1:16:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And because of history,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.32,1:16:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Marx was put in the great books of the rest of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.32,1:16:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,at 130.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.77,1:16:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Stands out like a sore thumb.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.38,1:16:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And the devastation of society
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.47,1:16:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is really Marxism in various disguises.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.85,1:16:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Which Marxism is so weak
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.85,1:16:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because it sees dualistically,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.85,1:16:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it sees everything in terms of perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.85,1:16:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you don't take responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.96,1:16:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're now weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.96,1:16:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why I'm sort of a champion of
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.23,1:16:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the former comedian
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.52,1:16:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,who goes around
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.52,1:16:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill Cosby, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.85,1:16:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Telling people, unless you accept responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.85,1:16:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the game is over, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.85,1:16:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.85,1:16:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.85,1:17:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's taking personal responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.85,1:17:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Marx says there isn't any.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.85,1:17:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is your fault
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.85,1:17:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because everything is the fault of something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.85,1:17:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's the downside of relativism
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.75,1:17:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates about 170 or 180.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.75,1:17:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And the philosophic schools that grew out of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.75,1:17:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's an anomaly.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.75,1:17:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,My favorite isn't even on here
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.75,1:17:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.75,1:17:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates at about 570.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.85,1:17:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get just a couple of concepts,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.85,1:17:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,everything else resolves.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.94,1:17:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You got the evolution of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.94,1:17:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that gets you off guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.14,1:17:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates will get you off the rest of the guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.14,1:17:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates never wrote any books.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.32,1:17:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He was short and ugly and bad to look at.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.32,1:17:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a mean wife, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.01,1:17:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates' wife, Xanthippe,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.01,1:18:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,had a sharp tongue
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.01,1:18:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and she's famous throughout history.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.01,1:18:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess he went into thinking this
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.01,1:18:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to get away from all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.10,1:18:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, from the dialogues of Plato and all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.10,1:18:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Socrates never wrote anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.10,1:18:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But Socrates at 570
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.10,1:18:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,got the whole principle,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.10,1:18:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,without it you don't even need the Course of Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.10,1:18:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates says that all men choose only the good.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.10,1:18:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The only problem is they don't know what is the good.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.88,1:18:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And they choose the illusory good for the real good.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.88,1:18:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They choose the temporary and temporal
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.88,1:18:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for that which is eternal.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.88,1:18:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see the basic innocence then.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.55,1:18:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see the basic innocence of man
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.68,1:18:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,by the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.68,1:18:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which you presented as it grew out of the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.68,1:18:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The best way to evolve,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.64,1:18:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.64,1:18:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is to take like one stanza
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.64,1:19:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 91st Psalm
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.64,1:19:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and just be with it all week.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.64,1:19:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next week take the next stanza.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.64,1:19:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you have Socrates' month.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.76,1:19:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So we could designate June
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.93,1:19:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,as Socrates' month.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.93,1:19:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The way, you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.22,1:19:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the way of enlightenment is contemplative.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.22,1:19:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditation will take you into Samadhi.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.22,1:19:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But then when you get up and uncross your legs
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.22,1:19:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and walk around the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.22,1:19:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the Samadhi disappears.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.52,1:19:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Contemplation takes you so that you become that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.52,1:19:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't disappear when you get up and walk around.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.52,1:19:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Contemplation is a lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.72,1:19:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,By intention you dedicate your life to God
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.72,1:19:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and your life thereby becomes a prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.84,1:19:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,As a manifestation of that prayer,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.86,1:19:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,then you revere
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.86,1:19:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of spiritual truth
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.86,1:20:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as it came down over the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.60,1:20:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you move forward to the other side,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.43,1:20:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,hang out with Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.56,1:20:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How's it going?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.43,1:20:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you did pretty good with it there.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.43,1:20:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You gave him a whole week on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.43,1:20:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You could have given him two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.88,1:20:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind chooses only the good.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.31,1:20:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If that includes blowing up a busload of children,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.02,1:20:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,don't you see, that's done for the good.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.34,1:20:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind chooses always what it deems to be the good.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.43,1:20:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's dominated by the animal,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.43,1:20:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,then gain is always the good.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.36,1:20:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The intrinsic innocence.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.90,1:20:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,From my own research,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.80,1:20:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,say the mind is like,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.89,1:21:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the human mind is like a computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.27,1:21:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The brain is your hardware,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.27,1:21:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the software is superimposed.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.46,1:21:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the hardware has no say
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.48,1:21:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,about what it gets programmed with.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.48,1:21:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll play anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.48,1:21:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether that's true or false,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.52,1:21:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the hardware has no way of knowing that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.52,1:21:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So people are programmed throughout life.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.06,1:21:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is intrinsically innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.06,1:21:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It cannot tell truth from falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.06,1:21:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because discernment doesn't occur
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.60,1:21:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,until the opening of the third eye of the Buddhic body.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.60,1:21:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,At that point, you're extremely advanced.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.60,1:21:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And by that time,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.60,1:21:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you have spiritual vision instead of perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.68,1:21:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual vision,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.71,1:21:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you get the totality and the feeling,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.71,1:21:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowingness of the essential truth of a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.71,1:21:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've done a lot of kinesiologic testing
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.93,1:21:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and calibrating of things,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.93,1:21:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you finally get to be sort of that way yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.93,1:21:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody gives you a book,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.38,1:21:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you look at it,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.38,1:22:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and you get,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.38,1:22:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I get what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.38,1:22:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about 280, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.38,1:22:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So you begin,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.52,1:22:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you become sensitive to the essence of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.52,1:22:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the mind is innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.69,1:22:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.69,1:22:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because their hardware cannot control
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.02,1:22:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the content of the software.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.02,1:22:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the miracle says that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.21,1:22:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ says that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.21,1:22:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha said that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.21,1:22:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Man has only one sin,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.78,1:22:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in quotes,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.78,1:22:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.97,1:22:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He does not know truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.97,1:22:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point in evolutionary time,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.30,1:22:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,emerging from the animal to the spiritual reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.39,1:22:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,80% of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.64,1:22:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is unable to discern truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.64,1:22:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.64,1:22:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind automatically then
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.64,1:22:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,chooses what it presumes to be the good.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.64,1:23:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That gives us a certain compassion
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.60,1:23:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,for all of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.60,1:23:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.60,1:23:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the relationship
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.60,1:23:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of the field of consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.60,1:23:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the context.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.60,1:23:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is content.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.60,1:23:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Content is linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.60,1:23:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Content is what differentiates a this from a that.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.85,1:23:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the limitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.31,1:23:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The limitation of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.31,1:23:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.31,1:23:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So the 400s represent the highest level
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.39,1:23:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of sophistication and handling,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.42,1:23:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,not the world but symbols of the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.42,1:23:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,mathematics and concepts,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.42,1:23:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,logic and reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.42,1:23:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The dialectic of reason
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.72,1:23:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is what has fallen into disrepute
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.81,1:23:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in academia.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.81,1:23:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So academia, which once calibrated
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.81,1:23:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in the mid-400s
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.81,1:23:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in many universities,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.97,1:24:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,has dropped to like 180 or 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.64,1:24:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest universities in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.64,1:24:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,have come down, down, down, down.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.64,1:24:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And they now teach a philosophy
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.68,1:24:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.68,1:24:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.68,1:24:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So education has come down over time.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.47,1:24:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.15,1:24:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.15,1:24:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.15,1:24:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the field that spontaneously brings into
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.15,1:24:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,actuality potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.88,1:24:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.88,1:24:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is spirit and this is ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.52,1:24:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.52,1:24:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirit, this is spirit and this is ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.84,1:24:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.84,1:24:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, today is on intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.22,1:24:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is Heisenberg Day.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.01,1:24:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now all the great saints of history
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.01,1:24:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't know anything about Heisenberg.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.60,1:24:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.60,1:25:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to be irrational
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.60,1:25:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to believe in prayer
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.68,1:25:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or the power of intention
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.68,1:25:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because now quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.84,1:25:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,has demonstrated that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.84,1:25:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a very important connection
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.84,1:25:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,between the intellect, reason, rationality.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.84,1:25:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And it gets you off being ridiculed
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.35,1:25:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,by the secularist or the intellectual.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.72,1:25:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, why are you believing
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.72,1:25:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in all that mystical, spiritual stuff?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.72,1:25:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And you tell them,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.76,1:25:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,look, I'm just busy collapsing,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.76,1:25:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,collapsing the potential.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.76,1:25:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm collapsing the wave function,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.92,1:25:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.27,1:25:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just putting into practice
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.10,1:25:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.10,1:25:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.10,1:25:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.10,1:25:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.71,1:25:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.71,1:25:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.43,1:25:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention is so powerful.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.43,1:25:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's see the difference
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.27,1:25:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,between intellectual observation,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.27,1:25:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectual observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.27,1:25:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Heisenberg principle
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.27,1:26:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,was based on scientific experiments.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.27,1:26:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you witness,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.27,1:26:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,observe the experiment,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.27,1:26:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you've already changed the result.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.27,1:26:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.27,1:26:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, so the power of that intention
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.09,1:26:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,would be correlated
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.09,1:26:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,with the consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.09,1:26:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,level of the observer.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.35,1:26:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That is correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.35,1:26:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.35,1:26:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.35,1:26:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.67,1:26:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So the power of the...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.69,1:26:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.69,1:26:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So the effect of the intention
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.69,1:26:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of the observer
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.23,1:26:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to depend
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.34,1:26:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,on the consciousness level.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.34,1:26:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew this years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.35,1:26:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I run a big clinic, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.35,1:26:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,real big.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.35,1:26:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And I hired psychiatrists,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.46,1:26:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,right and left therapists,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.46,1:26:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,psychologists, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.81,1:26:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And some doctors
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.81,1:26:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,just got everybody better.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.81,1:26:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And other doctors,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.22,1:26:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody seemed to get better.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.51,1:27:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the scientific design,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.67,1:27:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,then,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.67,1:27:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which sees causality,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.67,1:27:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it believes in pharmacology.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.67,1:27:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.02,1:27:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I can get double the recovery rate
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.02,1:27:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,with Prozac
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.02,1:27:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,than somebody else can with Prozac.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.02,1:27:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Easily.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.72,1:27:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Double.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.72,1:27:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.72,1:27:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.15,1:27:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.15,1:27:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Triple.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.15,1:27:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Quadruple.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.15,1:27:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten times.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.44,1:27:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten times.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.43,1:27:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.53,1:27:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten times the recovery rate
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.53,1:27:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,would be the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.32,1:27:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we try for ten?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.47,1:27:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.47,1:27:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The way we go over ten,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.97,1:27:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I know how it goes over ten.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.97,1:27:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm holding in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.97,1:27:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is a fact, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.97,1:27:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.97,1:27:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I would pray for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.97,1:27:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That jumped you way beyond ten.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.97,1:27:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.64,1:27:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So the consciousness level of...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.64,1:28:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the physician
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.64,1:28:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is not a mechanical pharmacologist.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.64,1:28:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a healer.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.72,1:28:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The modern paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.81,1:28:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,which is secular,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.81,1:28:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't see the physician
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.81,1:28:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,as a healer.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.81,1:28:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He sees them
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.81,1:28:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,as a provider of services.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.81,1:28:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A provider of services
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.15,1:28:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is lucky to get a 20% improvement
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.15,1:28:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,with Prozac.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.15,1:28:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.14,1:28:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The healer, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.76,1:28:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is the physician
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.76,1:28:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,whose caringness
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.76,1:28:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,about his patients
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.76,1:28:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is so powerful
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.76,1:28:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that anything will work
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.81,1:28:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that he prescribes for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.92,1:28:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we discovered that years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.52,1:28:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So the effect
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.76,1:28:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,on the result
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.76,1:28:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of the scientific experiment
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.76,1:28:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,reflects the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.76,1:28:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of the investigator
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.76,1:28:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and not the mechanism being tested.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.76,1:29:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That revolutionizes all of research.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.32,1:29:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell you,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.26,1:29:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in a research design,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.26,1:29:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the likelihood is success.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.93,1:29:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you tell me
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.31,1:29:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,who's going to do it,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.31,1:29:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I can guarantee to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.31,1:29:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.01,1:29:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So the power of the investigator
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.01,1:29:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is more powerful
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.01,1:29:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,than the design,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.01,1:29:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the scientific design.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.06,1:29:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Some physicians,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.06,1:29:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody gets better.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.86,1:29:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Other physicians,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.86,1:29:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,hardly anybody gets better.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.18,1:29:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Once in a while,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.18,1:29:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you get a hard nut.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.18,1:29:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I had one patient
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.18,1:29:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that never got better.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.39,1:29:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When I finally quit practice,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.39,1:29:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I threw up my hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.97,1:29:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.97,1:29:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy just won't get better.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.96,1:29:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Frustration.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.15,1:29:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.15,1:29:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I sent him to acupuncturists.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.15,1:29:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I did everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.15,1:29:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Chinese medicine,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.15,1:29:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,herbal energy balancing.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.15,1:29:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.36,1:30:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing ever made him feel better.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.36,1:30:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Even alcohol didn't feel better.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.93,1:30:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think that's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.93,1:30:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you have a few drinks
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.93,1:30:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or something?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.93,1:30:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.26,1:30:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he had a blood-brain barrier.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.96,1:30:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what you put
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.96,1:30:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in his bloodstream,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.96,1:30:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it somehow did not get
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.96,1:30:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,into his brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.96,1:30:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was the one guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.96,1:30:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember at the end
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.96,1:30:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when I quit practicing?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.96,1:30:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I hung out with all my old patients
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.96,1:30:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,until they all teetered over
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.96,1:30:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and died.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.96,1:30:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to desert them.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.18,1:30:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But this one guy,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.18,1:30:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to refer him
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.18,1:30:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Mayo Clinic.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.18,1:30:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I sent him to the Mayo Clinic.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.34,1:30:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.34,1:30:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.34,1:30:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Heisenberg principle then
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.78,1:30:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is that intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.78,1:30:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the field of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.78,1:30:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you saw it from content and field.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.78,1:30:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The field is so powerful
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.78,1:30:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that what you witness
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.46,1:30:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as your consciousness advances
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.46,1:30:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is that everything is fulfilling
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.46,1:30:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,its potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.46,1:30:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's becoming the actuality.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.46,1:31:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The actuality happens
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.46,1:31:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.46,1:31:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So your intention
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.46,1:31:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is what empowers it to happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.46,1:31:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,To devote yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.75,1:31:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to the search for enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.75,1:31:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for Christ consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.15,1:31:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever you want,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.15,1:31:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,self-realization,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.15,1:31:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to evolve spiritually
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.15,1:31:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is so powerful
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.15,1:31:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that it now aligns
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.15,1:31:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,everything in your life
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.15,1:31:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.38,1:31:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.07,1:31:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So we know that
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.07,1:31:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the Schrodinger equation
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.07,1:31:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,are both time-dependent
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.07,1:31:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and time-independent.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.94,1:31:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.60,1:31:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you introduce intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.98,1:31:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.98,1:31:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the universe is different.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.50,1:31:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You've collapsed the wave function,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.94,1:31:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the quantum mechanics way
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.94,1:31:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of saying what I've said
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.94,1:31:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,during lectures.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.94,1:32:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Potentiality becomes an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.19,1:32:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You've collapsed the wave function
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.19,1:32:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,by intention, by intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.19,1:32:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So the power of intention then
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.30,1:32:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is even more powerful
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.30,1:32:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,if the intention
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.30,1:32:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is instituted by a person
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.52,1:32:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,who is spiritually oriented.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.73,1:32:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.11,1:32:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So below 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.11,1:32:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the fulfillment of an intention
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.11,1:32:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is pretty much guided by
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.11,1:32:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the animal level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.11,1:32:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you get over 200 now,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.11,1:32:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you've pulled into the field
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.11,1:32:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,enormous power.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.11,1:32:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So a spiritual intention
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.11,1:32:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is an act of the will,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.25,1:32:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is a very, very powerful event,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.25,1:32:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has enormous karmic consequences.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.25,1:32:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.92,1:32:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The von Neumann process
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.92,1:32:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,gives you the details.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.10,1:32:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we said Einstein was at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.10,1:32:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud and Einstein both,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.10,1:32:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, refuted spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.35,1:32:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein was religious,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.48,1:33:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but he said,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.48,1:33:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,after the Soviet conference
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.48,1:33:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in Denmark, I think it was,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.75,1:33:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that he preferred to believe
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.75,1:33:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that there was an independent
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.75,1:33:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,existence out there,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.75,1:33:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,an independent universe
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.75,1:33:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that existed independently
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.75,1:33:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.35,1:33:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Independently of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.57,1:33:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.71,1:33:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And so he's,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.71,1:33:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,so at 499 is a paradigm jump,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.71,1:33:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigm jump,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.80,1:33:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,out of causality,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.80,1:33:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,out of,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.80,1:33:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and you move to subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.40,1:33:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So at 500,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.40,1:33:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you move to the level of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.96,1:33:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is provable
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.96,1:33:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is not spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.27,1:33:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirituality can be demonstrated,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.27,1:33:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,confirmed,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.27,1:33:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.27,1:33:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,verified,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.27,1:33:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but it cannot be proven.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.27,1:33:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot prove
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.78,1:33:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that somebody loves somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.78,1:33:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot prove.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.06,1:33:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is provable
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.26,1:34:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,belongs to the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.26,1:34:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.26,1:34:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of cause and effect,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.26,1:34:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.26,1:34:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.68,1:34:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So Einstein drew back from it,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.68,1:34:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, as did Freud.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.51,1:34:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud, I agreed with,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.51,1:34:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,as far as his,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.94,1:34:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that the images of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.23,1:34:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,are really projections
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.23,1:34:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,from the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.23,1:34:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So what he's talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.23,1:34:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is the negative depictions,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.23,1:34:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the satanic depictions
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.23,1:34:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of God of the Old Testament
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.23,1:34:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,as angry,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.23,1:34:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,capricious,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.23,1:34:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,paranoid,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.23,1:34:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,jealous,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.30,1:34:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,given to specialness,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.30,1:34:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,favoritism,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.30,1:34:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.30,1:34:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud said,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.30,1:34:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that's on the unconscious
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.30,1:34:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and projected on the divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.30,1:34:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So because he disproved
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.30,1:34:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the reality of
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.30,1:34:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,an actual truthful divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.30,1:34:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,he then falsely concluded,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.30,1:34:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore, there was no divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.30,1:34:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that the way you depicted it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.68,1:34:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is false,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.68,1:34:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and the limitation of that
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.68,1:34:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,would have been
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.68,1:35:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the false depictions of God
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.68,1:35:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,are false
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.68,1:35:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and arise out of
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.68,1:35:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the collective unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.68,1:35:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Primitive man,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.68,1:35:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,when the thunder rolled
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.68,1:35:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and the volcano erupted,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.68,1:35:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,he sacrificed more maidens.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.68,1:35:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mayan and Aztecs
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.03,1:35:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated about 90.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.03,1:35:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You know the priests
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.03,1:35:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,were so busy?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.60,1:35:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Busy.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.60,1:35:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How many hearts
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.60,1:35:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,they could rip out per hour?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.31,1:35:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands were lined up
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.43,1:35:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,for centuries.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.43,1:35:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Those religions calibrated 90.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.50,1:35:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.68,1:35:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So Einstein then pulled back.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.68,1:35:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So there you have
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.55,1:35:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,what's called
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.55,1:35:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the paradigm blindness.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.55,1:35:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So much of science,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.55,1:35:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,journals on science
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.57,1:35:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and religion,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.57,1:35:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,science and consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.57,1:35:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the paradigm of blindness.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.64,1:35:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Religion, science,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.64,1:35:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.64,1:35:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.64,1:35:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And conferences,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.64,1:35:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because I've spoken at them.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.64,1:35:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're stuck in that paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.71,1:35:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can't prove one paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.71,1:36:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,by the tools of another.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.71,1:36:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't find
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.02,1:36:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,ghosts with a Geiger counter.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.47,1:36:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what science is doing,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.47,1:36:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is trying to find
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.47,1:36:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,ghosts with a Geiger counter,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.47,1:36:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because the intellect
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.47,1:36:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is not the tool
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.47,1:36:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to investigate
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.47,1:36:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,or verify spiritual realities.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.60,1:36:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There you have to deal with
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.60,1:36:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of the mystics,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.60,1:36:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and people who have
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.60,1:36:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,subjectively experienced.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.60,1:36:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.69,1:36:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.69,1:36:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.72,1:36:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.72,1:36:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.64,1:36:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,this is very important,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.89,1:36:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because what happens
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.89,1:36:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,at consciousness level,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.89,1:36:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.89,1:36:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,without the avatars,
